title: Dada Thakur
subTitle: Gita plans to reunite with her long-estranged father, not knowing that he is waiting for her younger sister, Mita, to return. The two siblings then struggle to win back his trust.

title: Rater Rajani Gandha
subTitle: After her father's death, Anuradha is accused of insanity and escapes to Kolkata. There, she crosses paths with Raja, setting off a chain of life-altering events.

title: Shiv Shakti
subTitle: To propose marriage on behalf of Lord Shiva, the gods pay a visit to Parvati's parents. However, Mainadevi, Parvati's mother, declines the proposal.

title: Gangstar King
subTitle: Prem, a dreaded gangster, uses a simple call centre employee's guise to live with a family as a paying guest. However, his housemates are unaware of his evil motives.

title: Raja Babu
subTitle: Raja, a rich but illiterate young man, falls for Madhu after seeing her photographs and she mistakes him for a lawyer. Things turn ugly when she discovers the truth, leading to chaos and heartbreak.

title: Nawab Nandini
subTitle: Nabab and Nandini, once childhood sweethearts, meet again in college and fall in love despite their differences.

title: Champion
subTitle: A lazy man must rise to the occasion when his brother lands in trouble. However, with two beautiful women chasing after him, the man struggles to make the right decisions.

title: Minister Phatakesto
subTitle: Fatakeshto, an MLA turned home minister, vows to rescue the government from a massive financial loss while political thugs create several hurdles for him.

title: Nater Guru
subTitle: A terrible heart attack leaves Sulochana in a vulnerable position. To ease her burdens, Sulochana's daughter reaches out to her estranged husband for help.

title: Indrajit
subTitle: Indrajit is an honest police officer who punishes Raja, an MLA's son, for raping a girl. The MLA then kidnaps the former's son and demands Raja's release.

title: Indrajit
subTitle: Indrajit is an honest police officer who punishes Raja, an MLA's son, for raping a girl. The MLA then kidnaps the former's son and demands Raja's release.

title: Sadhanpith Tarapith
subTitle: Tarapith, a town famous for its Kali temple, witnesses many miracles due to its extraordinary history. Due to its famous legend, thousands of devout people offer their blessings on a yearly basis.

title: Shiv Shakti
subTitle: When Mainadevi rejects Lord Shiva's marriage proposal, Parvati is left astounded, and Diti and Tarakasura are delighted by Mainadevi's decision.

title: Prem Shakti
subTitle: Ganga and Gauri anger an evil tantric by saving Nagaraj. Enraged, the tantric turns Gauri into stone and kills Ganga. Nagaraj blesses Ganga with rebirth and helps unite him with his love.

title: Gariber Samman
subTitle: Being the eldest daughter, Madhavi takes up the responsibility of uniting the family during hard times. She sacrifices her love and happiness to protect the honour of the family.

title: Dui Prithibi
subTitle: A rich man falls in love with an idealistic medical student. However, when circumstances force them apart, he learns the true meaning and value of love.

title: Poran Jaye Jolia Re
subTitle: A young man, Rabin, meets three different women at different stages in his life. The relationship he shares with these women, though very different from each other, help him grow as a person.

title: Premer Kahini
subTitle: Akash falls in love with Barsha but loses contact with her due to unforeseeable circumstances. While attending a marriage ceremony, he is shocked to realise that the bride is none other than Barsha.

title: Pratibad
subTitle: A fierce fighter against injustice strives to help his middle-class family make ends meet. His dedication lands him a job as a police officer, where he tackles large-scale problems with determination.

title: Dujone
subTitle: Akash is the son of a rich industrialist who falls in love with a poor girl and intends to marry her. Soon, their families find out and start opposing their relationship.

title: Dujone

title: Mrs. Sen
subTitle: When her husband Somnath meets with an accident, Anuradha flies to Thailand to see him and is shocked to see his second wife and son.

title: Shiv Shakti
subTitle: Parvati decides to sacrifice her love against her will to make her parents feel content. Lord Shiva goes on a disguise in order to meet Parvati.

title: Ami Subhash Bolchi
subTitle: Debabrata Bose, a conflicted man, awakens the spirit of late Bengali patriot Netaji Subhas Chandra Bose as he fights for change and strives to unite his Bengali community.

title: Sansar Sangram
subTitle: The death of his father leaves Anand's life in sudden sorrow and upheaval. Soon, he navigates the challenges of supporting his family on his own two shoulders.

title: Behula Lakhindar
subTitle: An arrogant man who is against theism refuses to acknowledge a Goddess in her mortal avatar. Later, she teaches him a lesson to accept her divinity.

title: Chhoto Bou
subTitle: A mother-in-law treats her daughters-in-law, Mamta, Tandra and Deepa, according to their husband's income. However, when she falls ill, she realises her folly.

title: Sedin Dekha Hoyechilo
subTitle: Kavita's father holds his daughter's lover's friends captive and asks them to reveal the couple's whereabouts. However, one of the boys, Abir, falls in love with his other daughter, Nandini.

title: Premi
subTitle: Sumit, a football player, loses his leg while trying to save Rahul, his best friend. Fate plays a cruel joke when the girl Rahul loves is about to be married off to Sumit.

title: Ke Tumi Nandini
subTitle: Nandini, a free-spirited girl who aspires to be a medical student, develops feelings for a man named Abir. Furthermore, she strives to impress him, but he appears to reject her advances.
